HEADWORD: Silundum
<hw>Si*lun"dum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <mark>[Trade
name]</mark> <def>A form of silicon carbide, produced in the electric
furnace, possessing great hardness, and high electrical resistance, and
not subject to oxidation below 2880⟦deg⟧ F., or 1600⟦deg⟧ C.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

